        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} Here we got drinks, breakfast for the next few days, and some small items. Then we went to the Rollin Pin Cafe, which was at least familiar to Basti, and had a proper breakfast there. Basti got some work done while I passed the time reading. As it approached noon, we took a tricycle back to the hostel for the 12 PM check-out. </p>
        <p> After everything was done there, we went to the bus station and luckily the right bus was ready - and it was air-conditioned! We even found two seats together. You have to be lucky! Behind us sat a family who clearly had fun with us Europeans, especially when we reacted and joined in the fun. After the journey started, the ticket collector came around pretty quickly and handed out tickets to everyone. Payment is only collected in the second round, after everyone has been taken care of. After collecting the fares, his third round followed: giving back change! Amazingly, he always knew exactly who gave him what! I would be hopelessly lost. </p>
