        <p> When we arrived in Zamboanguita, we were immediately picked up by a tricycle driver who was supposed to take us to the resort on a fairly new machine with plenty of horsepower. He wanted to show off the power right away and was visibly proud of it, but we politely asked him to slow down! The remaining meters off the main road went over a sandy, bumpy slope until we finally arrived. Unfortunately, our room wasn't ready yet, so we treated ourselves to cold drinks and watched the beach. Sadly, this section of the beach turned out to be very rocky in the sea, but luckily there are alternative options to the left or right. After we moved into our room a short time later - small, nice, and above all clean - we went back to the bar. Basti started working and I found a nice spot to enjoy for now. Nothing else happened that day, except for a good lunch/dinner. </p>
